- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the time complexity of the proposed algorithm and compares it with existing algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with string compression, which involves discrete mathematical concepts such as combinatorics and graph theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper mentions rational scoring functions, which are related to information theory and coding theory. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as edit-distance is a commonly used metric in natural language processing and machine learning, and the paper proposes a new algorithm for computing it efficiently.
